4:
Gah... This isn't over yet! I can still...
fight!
14:
He is in bad shape, but it's nothing
life-threatening. We should get him
bandaged and to a doctor,
immediately.
17:
Leave me be! I can... 
I can do this myself...
21:
Pipe down, pal. Save it for when we
get outta here.
24: I sense an Oudo of great pain...
28: Hi! Nice to meet you, I'm Elmor!
41:
Thank... you? Uh... Did you just come
out of the floor?
45: I sensed a very, very strong Oudo.
48:
There was this rift-thing... a branch
of the Kaleidoscope, I think? It was
just under here.
51:
You should be okay now. No more
ouchies for you.
57: Oudo... So she used her Spirit Horns.
61: Your Oudo... You're still in pain. Why?
65:
While I appreciate the healing, you
should just leave me. Just leave me
like everyone—
77:
He's still hurt... Not on the outside,
but on the inside.
83:
Wh-what are you talking about?!
You don't know me! Y-you don't
know how I feel!
86:
But I do. Your Oudo tells me
everything.
89:
You've been all alone... So lonely... 
It must've been hard.
95:
It's okay. You don't need to act
strong anymore. You did a good job,
and I'm proud of you.
98:
What are you TALKING about?! 
I... I'm NOT...
103:
You don't have to hold it in. You're
safe now.
109: I think someone needs a hug.
112:
I... I just... All this time, I've had to
tough it out on my own! I'm just... 
So damn awkward, I could never 
make any friends, and—!
121:
Uh... I'm pretty sure that's the power
of the Spirit Horns...
125:
Can't imagine what it'd be like if they
got used on you. Eugh...
130:
That being said... He may be the
better for it. Though... I can't quite
say for sure...
144:
What, EXACTLY, was it that you were
THINKING?!
147:
Your job is to investigate the
branches of the Kaleidoscope, is it
not? So why is it that you are using
your Spirit Horns to bond with a
human?!
151:
I-I'm sorry, Lady Memram. I... I just
wanted to better understand them.
155:
And this is how you chose to go
about it?
158:
There's this saying: "A true
swordsman gives their life for those
who believe in them." I think I finally
understand that now.
160:
Like many in our cohort, you were
saved by Lady Elmor in more ways
than one. Praise be!
163:
I guess she's done this sort of thing
before.
167:
What can I say? Adventuring is a
dangerous profession. If someone's
offering free therapy, I'm not going
to stop them.
171:
Adventurers that feel better, perform
better. And most importantly, I keep
getting paid! I'd say that's a win-win
situation.
176:
That's not true. Your Oudo doesn't
care about money, you're just
relieved that people are feeling
better—
181:
H-hey! Reading my Oudo is OFF
LIMITS!
194:
Humans are not like us Vesta, Elmor.
You should not read their Oudo so
carelessly. I have warned you before.
199:
Aww... But, that's not fair. You did it
too, didn't you Lady Memram? With
the Hero of the Red Soup's—
204: That has nothing to do with this.
207:
...However, you have a point.
Perhaps it is time that you learn
proper judgment.
212:
Yes, ma'am! I'm gonna learn how to
use my powers!
216:
So, hero... I trust that you will see it
through.
221:
Yeah, sure—wait, what? What do you
mean?
225:
You will take care of Elmor. I believe
you are more than capable.
232:
Thank you! I'm gonna make sooo
many friends with all kinds of people!
235:
You're gonna introduce me, right? 
I wanna make as many friends 
as I can!
